"title": "7447: slavery, in OT",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7447: slavery, in ot",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Slavery in the OT occurs when someone either voluntarily or forcibly becomes completely subject to another person's control.</p>\n<h2>Reasons for slavery</h2>\n<h3>War</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut20:10-Deut20:11\">DEU 20:10–20:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:21\">GEN 14:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:9\">NUM 31:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:2\">2KI 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:8\">2CH 28:8</a></p>\n<h3>Purchase</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:44-Lev25:45\">LEV 25:44–25:45</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:23-Gen37:28\">GEN 37:23–37:28</a></p>\n<h3>Debt</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:1\">2KI 4:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:2-Exod22:3\">EXO 22:2–22:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:39\">LEV 25:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:47-Lev25:48\">LEV 25:47–25:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:12\">DEU 15:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:1-Neh5:5\">NEH 5:1–5:5</a></p>\n<h3>Birth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:4\">EXO 21:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:12-Gen17:13\">GEN 17:12–17:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:7\">ECC 2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:14\">JER 2:14</a></p>\n<h3>Conscription of foreigners as forced labour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:29-2Sam12:31\">2SA 12:29–12:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod1:11-Exod1:14\">EXO 1:11–1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh9:22-Josh9:23\">JOS 9:22–9:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh16:10\">JOS 16:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:28\">JDG 1:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:20-1Kgs9:21\">1KI 9:20–9:21</a></p>\n<h2>Rights of slaves</h2>\n<h3>Rights of protection against physical and sexual abuse</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:43\">LEV 25:43</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:7-Exod21:11\">EXO 21:7–21:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:20-Exod21:21\">EXO 21:20–21:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:26-Exod21:27\">EXO 21:26–21:27</a></p>\n<h3>Rights to participate in religious feasts and festivals</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:12\">EXO 23:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:9-Exod20:10\">EXO 20:9–20:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:11-Deut12:12\">DEU 12:11–12:12</a></p>\n<h3>Rights to inherit property</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:3\">GEN 15:3</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Rights of asylum</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:15\">DEU 23:15</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The release of slaves</h2>\n<h3>Release in the Year of Jubilee</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:54-Lev25:55\">LEV 25:54–25:55</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:39-Lev25:41\">LEV 25:39–25:41</a></p>\n<h3>Release after six years of service</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:2\">EXO 21:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:3-Exod21:6\">EXO 21:3–21:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:12-Deut15:18\">DEU 15:12–15:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer34:8-Jer34:20\">JER 34:8–34:20</a> <em>The six-year principle was being abused in the time of Jeremiah.</em></p>\n<h3>Release through redemption by a near relative</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:47-Lev25:53\">LEV 25:47–25:53</a></p>\n<h2>The status of slaves</h2>\n<h3>Slaves as property</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:46\">LEV 25:46</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:32\">EXO 21:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:39-Lev25:42\">LEV 25:39–25:42</a> <em>Fellow Israelites were not to be regarded as property.</em></p>\n<h3>Slaves as trusted advisors</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam9:5-1Sam9:10\">1SA 9:5–9:10</a></p>",
